Zimbabwe Agency Invests $179 Million in Banks, Newsday Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-08-01T12:06:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/zimbabwe-agency-invests-179-million-in-banks-newsday-reports.html
Zimbabwe ’s National Social Security
Agency invested $179 million in Zimbabwean banks to boost
lending,  Newsday  reported, citing  NSSA  general manager James
Matiza.  Banks will use to money to provide loans of between
$200,000 and $5 million for periods of as much as a year, the
Harare-based newspaper cited Matiza as saying on its website.
The agency, formed to pay  unemployment benefits , invested in 20
financial institutions and 64 of Zimbabwe’s 78 listed companies,
it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
